cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR 

This paper deals with learning representations for sentiment analysis in NLP tasks, which falls under the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the challenges of finding such representations and proposes metrics to assess model robustness, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of data filtering and bias in datasets, which can be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) tasks.
